Hello,

Thanks for giving the hints. I am trying the following command –

cmake -DCMAKE_C_COMPILER="C:\Program Files (x86)\IntelSWTools\parallel_studio_xe_2019\compilers_and_libraries_2019\windows\bin\intel64" -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER="C:\Program Files (x86)\IntelSWTools\parallel_studio_xe_2019\compilers_and_libraries_2019\windows\bin\intel64" -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release


But it is not generating the binaries.


Thanks,
Joy

Hi @joyintel,  

It's a commercial software, I don't have it, so I can't reproduce your error. Sorry. 

Could you please post the full build log here?

Maybe it should instead be (add icl.exe to the parameters instead of just the directory):

cmake -DCMAKE_C_COMPILER="C:\Program Files (x86)\IntelSWTools\parallel_studio_xe_2019\compilers_and_libraries_2019\windows\bin\intel64\**icl.exe**" -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER="C:\Program Files (x86)\IntelSWTools\parallel_studio_xe_2019\compilers_and_libraries_2019\windows\bin\intel64\**icl.exe**" -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release

I have given the trace here. The build is successful but there are no binaries (onnxruntime_perf_test.exe) created in the specified directory.

I have tried to use the CMAKE_C_COMPILER and CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER flags. But every time MSVC is selected instead.
